  <p>
    Engrams provides tools to estimate and forecast your token usage:
  </p>

  <h3>Estimate Context Size</h3>
  <pre><code>engrams estimate-context --task "Add JWT authentication"

Estimated context:
├── Semantic matches: 8 items (~1,200 tokens)
├── Tag matches: 3 items (~400 tokens)
├── Code bindings: 2 items (~300 tokens)
├── Glossary terms: 5 items (~200 tokens)
└── Total: ~2,100 tokens

Cost per request: $0.0063
Recommended budget: 4,000 tokens (plenty of room)</code></pre>

  <h3>Forecast Monthly Costs</h3>
  <pre><code>engrams forecast-costs --requests-per-day 50 --days 30

Forecast:
├── Average context per request: 2,100 tokens
├── Daily cost: $0.315
├── Monthly cost: $9.45
├── Yearly cost: $113.40

Comparison:
├── Without budgeting: $270/year
├── With budgeting: $113/year
└── Annual savings: $157</code></pre>

  <h2>Optimization Strategies</h2>
  <p>
    Here are practical ways to optimize your context budgeting:
  </p>

  <h3>1. Use Code Bindings</h3>
  <p>
    Bind decisions and patterns to specific code paths. When you edit a file, only relevant context loads:
  </p>
  <pre><code>engrams bind --decision 7 --pattern "src/auth/**/*.py"

Now when you edit src/auth/middleware.py:
Decision #7 (JWT auth) loads automatically
Unrelated decisions (database, caching) don't load
Context is smaller, cost is lower</code></pre>

  <h3>2. Tag Strategically</h3>
  <p>
    Use consistent tags so semantic search works better:
  </p>
  <pre><code>Decision: "Use PostgreSQL for primary database"
Tags: ["database", "architecture", "persistence"]

Decision: "Use Redis for caching"
Tags: ["caching", "performance", "infrastructure"]

Now searching for "persistence" finds the PostgreSQL decision.
Searching for "performance" finds the Redis decision.</code></pre>

  <h3>3. Archive Old Decisions</h3>
  <p>
    Mark decisions as "archived" so they don't clutter searches:
  </p>
  <pre><code>engrams archive-decision 15 --reason "Superseded by Decision #42"

Archived decisions:
- Don't appear in semantic search results
- Don't count toward token budget
- Still available if you search explicitly
- Maintain audit trail</code></pre>

  <h3>4. Adjust Budget by Task Type</h3>
  <p>
    Different tasks need different amounts of context:
  </p>
  <pre><code>engrams set-budget --task-type "bug-fix" --tokens 2000
engrams set-budget --task-type "new-feature" --tokens 4000
engrams set-budget --task-type "refactor" --tokens 3000

Now Engrams automatically uses the right budget for each task.</code></pre>

  <h3>5. Use Glossaries Efficiently</h3>
  <p>
    Glossary terms are cheap (low token count) but valuable. Use them for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Domain-specific terminology</li>
    <li>API schemas and data structures</li>
    <li>Common abbreviations and acronyms</li>
    <li>Team conventions</li>
  </ul>

